            {
                "s2_paper_id": "f4cd61f20c64535d03bd443ef075e989858b18b1",
                "title": "The ${\\rm BMO}\\to{\\rm BLO}$ action of the maximal operator on $\\alpha$-trees.",
                "year": 2019,
                "venue": "",
                "citation_count": 0,
                "reference_count": 18,
                "abstract": "We obtain the explicit upper Bellman function for the natural dyadic maximal operator acting from ${\\rm BMO}(\\mathbb{R}^n)$ into ${\\rm BLO}(\\mathbb{R}^n).$ As a consequence, we show that the ${\\rm BMO}\\to{\\rm BLO}$ norm of the natural operator equals 1 for all $n,$ and so does the norm of the classical dyadic maximal operator. The main result is a partial corollary of a theorem for the so-called $\\alpha$-trees, which generalize dyadic lattices. The Bellman function in this setting exhibits an interesting quasi-periodic structure depending on $\\alpha,$ but also allows a majorant independent of $\\alpha,$ hence the dimension-free norm constant. We also describe the decay of the norm with respect to the difference between the average of a function on a cube and the infimum of its maximal function on that cube. An explicit norm-optimizing sequence is constructed.",
                "authors": [
                    {
                        "s2_author_id": "89709253",
                        "name": "Adam Osc\u0229kowski"
                    },
                    {
                        "s2_author_id": "38790176",
                        "name": "L. Slavin"
                    },
                    {
                        "s2_author_id": "88897593",
                        "name": "V. Vasyunin"
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
